tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE quantum_gate_operations (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    gate_name VARCHAR(50),
    operation_type VARCHAR(50),
    qubit_order INT,
    gate_result VARCHAR(100)
)

CREATE TABLE QuantumGatesOperations (
  id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  gate_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
  operation_type VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
  quantum_states TEXT,
  execution_time TIMESTAMP
);

CREATE TABLE QuantumGatesResults (
  id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  operation_id INT,
  result_state TEXT,
  execution_status VARCHAR(20) NOT NULL,
  execution_time TIMESTAMP,
  FOREIGN KEY (operation_id) REFERENCES QuantumGatesOperations(id)
);

CREATE TABLE gate_operations (
    operation_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    gate_id UUID REFERENCES quantum_gates(gate_id),
    operation_type VARCHAR(50),
    success BOOLEAN,
    execution_time INT
);

CREATE TABLE gate_mapping (
    mapping_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    gate_id INT,
    circuit_id INT,
    qubit_id INT,
    mapping_description TEXT
);
